🎯 Project Goal

Create a Python script that:

Automatically organizes files into folders

Example:

Images → images/

Text files → docs/

Videos → videos/

🧠 Concept Used

os → file handling

shutil → move files

loops

conditions

👉 This project combines real skills.

🛠️ Step-by-Step Code
import os
import shutil

source_folder = "your_folder_path"

# Folder names
folders = {
    "images": [".jpg", ".png"],
    "docs": [".txt", ".pdf"],
    "videos": [".mp4", ".mkv"]
}

for file in os.listdir(source_folder):
    file_path = os.path.join(source_folder, file)

    if os.path.isfile(file_path):
        for folder, extensions in folders.items():
            if file.endswith(tuple(extensions)):
                
                dest_folder = os.path.join(source_folder, folder)

                if not os.path.exists(dest_folder):
                    os.makedirs(dest_folder)

                shutil.move(file_path, dest_folder)
📌 How It Works

1️⃣ Loop through all files
2️⃣ Check file type
3️⃣ Create folder if not exists
4️⃣ Move file to correct folder

